cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a novel attention-driven multi-branch network that learns robust and discriminative human representation, which involves deep learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also uses datasets for evaluation, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper involves designing an intra-attention network and an inter-attention module, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with optimizing person ReID, which involves information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category.
